Multi-Factor Equity Research Framework
Quantitative Asset Management Research Project

A quantitative equity research framework designed to investigate whether common equity factors can explain stock returns and generate risk-adjusted excess performance.

The project evaluates a multi-factor investment strategy combining:

Momentum
Quality
Low Volatility

The objective is to build, backtest and analyze a systematic factor portfolio using historical market data.

Research Question

Which equity factors explain stock returns?

The research investigates whether stocks with stronger characteristics:

higher past returns
higher profitability
lower volatility

can generate superior portfolio performance.

Strategy Overview

The framework follows a standard quantitative asset management workflow:

Calculate factor signals
Normalize factor scores
Build composite ranking
Select portfolio constituents
Backtest historical performance
Evaluate risk-adjusted returns
Perform CAPM risk analysis
Dataset
Universe

Large-cap US equities.

Sample period:

2015-01-02 → 2025-12-30

Frequency:

Daily prices

Portfolio rebalance:

Monthly
Factor Construction
1. Momentum Factor

Momentum measures historical price strength.

Formula:

Momentum =
Price(t) / Price(t-252) - 1

Stocks with stronger previous 12-month performance receive higher scores.

2. Low Volatility Factor

Low volatility identifies stocks with more stable return behavior.

Formula:

Volatility =
Std(Returns) × sqrt(252)

Lower volatility receives a higher score.

3. Quality Factor

Quality is measured using Return on Equity (ROE).

Formula:

ROE =
Net Income / Shareholder Equity

Companies with stronger profitability receive higher quality rankings.

Composite Factor Model

Each factor is transformed into percentile rankings.

The final score:

Composite Score =

40% Momentum

+

30% Quality

+

30% Low Volatility

Stocks are ranked from highest to lowest composite score.

Portfolio Construction
Long Portfolio

The strategy invests in the top 20% ranked stocks.

Characteristics:

Equal weighted
Monthly rebalance
Systematic stock selection
Backtesting Methodology

At each rebalance date:

Calculate historical factor values
Rank all stocks
Select top-ranked securities
Hold portfolio for one month
Rebalance

This approach avoids look-ahead bias.

Performance Results
Factor Portfolio Performance
Metric	Result
Annual Return	16.77%
Sharpe Ratio	1.01
Maximum Drawdown	-20.90%
CAPM Analysis

The portfolio was evaluated using the Capital Asset Pricing Model.

Model:

Rp - Rf = α + β(Rm - Rf) + ε

Results:

Metric	Value
Alpha	-0.001288
Beta	0.874
R²	0.577
Alpha p-value	0.681
Interpretation

The multi-factor portfolio generated attractive historical returns with a Sharpe ratio above 1.

The portfolio characteristics indicate:

Moderate risk-adjusted performance
Lower market sensitivity
Defensive exposure through low volatility

However, CAPM analysis shows that the estimated alpha is not statistically significant.

This suggests that the observed performance may be explained by factor exposure rather than persistent market-independent alpha.

Dashboard

The project includes an interactive Streamlit research dashboard.

Features:

Portfolio performance metrics
Cumulative return visualization
Monthly return distribution
Research statistics

Run:

streamlit run app/streamlit.py
